<br>
<br>
1) Sky Shrine - ***** of Benevolence quests, Spirit of Garzicor, and Circlet of Fallikan. All nice items and easily doable with some outside work on the person wanting the item <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2) Maiden's Eye in the Fort - take on the fort some decent gear drops here mostly good for selling but you might equip some of the melee, Also the named that you ll be hoping to spawn (you need to kill PH's) drops some very decent stuff<br>
<br>
3) UP named - think this one would be  challenge to you guys but well within your means and gets you a chance at some FT items and really nice melee junk :P<br>
<br>
4) The Deep - decent stuff drops there and its an ok zone different anyhow. prolly take some effort to get organized <br>
<br>
5) Siren's Grotto - Very nice place and will give you all a feeling for underwater fighting, which is a necessary evil for some reason. Also decent things can drop but they are on named so gotta hope they pop with what you want heh<br>
<br>
6) Dragon's in Western Waste - no lying these guys are a blast to do! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  And very important will get you at least semi prepared fo the next step up.  Most of them AE with Dispell so be prepared, and need to keep eyes out for adds and all that. As a side note make sure you know what your attacking becuase if your not ready and you get Silenced ... GAME OVER :P<br>
<br>
Think thats about all I can add (and some where already listed Ahkeva is fun)<br>
<br>
Just focus on levels and the rest will come... You really do need a chanter or two though, dont worry bout the Pally tanking a good SK with some AA's behind him is a hell of a force, if he's a gnome Pally though just /guildremove and save yourself the trouble :P ROFL<br>
<br>
Ethari <br>
61st mage<br>
